{{About|the strip cartoonist and creator of ''The Gambols''|the comics artist|Barrie Appleby}} {{Infobox comics creator <!-- | name = Barry Appleby --> | image = | imagesize = | caption = | alt = | birth_name = | birth_date ={{Birth date|1909|08|30|df=y}} | birth_place = | death_place = | nationality = British | area = | cartoonist = 1 | write = | art = | pencil = | ink = | edit = | publish = | letter = | color = | alias = | signature = <!-- very optional --> | signature_alt = | notable works = ''[[The Gambols]]'' | awards = | website = | subcat = British | death_date={{Death date and age|1996|03|11|1909|08|30|df=y}} }} '''Barry Appleby''' (30 August 1909 – 11 March 1996) was a British cartoonist famous for creating ''[[The Gambols]]'' for the ''[[Daily Express]]''. The strip premiered on 16 March 1950. The script was written by his wife Dobs, and was based on their own lives.
Appleby's father, E J. Appleby, was in the 1940s the editor of [[Autocar (magazine)|Autocar]], a leading British motor magazine,<ref name=Autocar196611>{{cite journal| authorlink = Dennis May|title = The Barrydobb| journal = [[Autocar (magazine)|Autocar]] | volume = | pages = 1130–1131|date = 25 November 1966 }}</ref> and one to which Appleby himself contributed his first illustration in 1931.<ref name=Autocar196611/> Later Appleby also wrote for the magazine edited by his father, using the alias "Helix".<ref name=Autocar196611/>
==References== *Strickler, Dave. ''Syndicated Comic Strips and Artists, 1924-1995: The Complete Index.'' Cambria, CA: Comics Access, 1995. {{ISBN|0-9700077-0-1}}.
